718806f-a.title: Manhattan: Canal Street - Chrystie Street
718806f-a.text:
A general view northward along Chrystie (left) and Forsyth (right)
Streets, from the Manhattan Bridge, at Canal Street, and showing clearance
for the Sarah Delano Roosevelt Park. Intersecting streets, shown in the ord)r
of their appearance, are Hester, Grand, Broome, Delancey, Rivington, Stanton
and East Houston.
January 14, 1932.
International News Photo.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

723049f-a.title: Manhattan: Canal Street - Chrystie Street
723049f-a.text:
Roosevelt (Sarah Delano) Park: Two views of the southern and of the cleared
area that will form this East Side park. Chrystie Street bounds same
on the right and Forsyth Street on the left. These photographs are
in a southward direction to Canal Street and show the columnaded entrance
to the Manhattan Bridge at that point. View 1 is from Broome Street,
while No. 2 is from Hester Street.
October 7, 1930.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
